 Watson for Lillees Chennai camp

Mumbai: Australian allrounder Shane Watson will attend a 12-day camp under Dennis Lillee at Chennais Pace Foundation, beginning later this week, in a bid to combat injuries. 

A member of the squad that completed a hattrick of World Cup titles in the Caribbean two months ago, tThe 26-year-old has suffered stress-related injuries in his back, hamstring and calves. 

He is coming here to straighten his technique and work with Lillee, Pace Foundation coach T.A. Sekar, a former India fast bowler and national selector, said on Tuesday. 

